The Project n. º 00074022 - UNDP/Spain MDG Achievement Fund - Joint Programme "Food and Nutrition Security of Indigenous Children and Women in Brazil" aims to contribute to guaranteeing the food and nutrition security of vulnerable indigenous children and women in the municipality of Dourados  Mato Grosso do Sul state (MS), and in Alto Solimões region (Alto Solimões River)  Amazonas state (AM), Brazil. 
According to the project document, UNDP CO of Brazil will have to directly execute the amount of US$ 885.008 in the three year period, to be executed specifically through three outcomes:
(1) Improved food and nutrition security for indigenous children and women in the Alto Rio Solimões (Amazonas) region and Dourados municipality (Mato Grosso do Sul) of Brazil;
(2) Empowered Indigenous Peoples able to demand their human right to adequate food and the right to health, and public institutions trained and strengthened to carry out their duties; 
(3) Diagnosis, monitoring and assessment of the food and nutrition security of indigenous populations carried out.
